         I just did this, but unfortunately I didn't keep as good a record as I should have. I started out apprehensive, but I had hunted in the Overthere from about 38 to 44, and did this quest several times for XP while I was there. So once I restarted for the mallet, It only took about 5 sets (20 braids). Then maybe 12-20 more sets (48-80) to get from Indifferent to Amiable.</P><P>You need to be Amiable to complete the quest. You also have to be level 50 to use the mallet.</P><P>There are several Sarnak ruins which are good for harvesting braids, but it still takes some time. I camped the one to the north east of the zone for maybe 5 hours total in several sessions to go from high apprehensive to amiable. </P><P>My question is: Is there anyway to recover from being KoS at the outpost? My SK got the mallet a while ago and then idiotically destroyed his faction there, so I always have to fight the skel in the boat and then sneak out. I'd love to fix it up. I'm much more faction concious now, though my necro is hated just about everywhere. Thank goodness for gather shadows!</P><P>Oh, how many shadowmen will I have to kill to repair my "Your standing with the TempleofSolRo couldn't possibly get any worse"? Those Ortallius days are coming back to haunt me!</P><P>Good luck with the Mallet!</P><P>Nefariette<BR>51 Heretic<BR>E'ci</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
