         And word to the wise: Single pull them out of the ruins. If you send in your pet, the others will gang up on him and then on you. Even at 50 these guys dropped me once (*still kicking myself*).</P><P>Pull with darkness and you'll always get one, once they're outside the fort you can send in the pet and you're good to go. If there's a caster the trick is to get as far away as you can and still cast darkness, then he'll get pissed, and try to cast on you, but immediately after casting darkness you'll take a few steps backwards so you'll be out of his casting range, he'll then come after you, his spell will hit and your pet will charge in, but he'll be outside the ruins and the aggro radius of the others. The radius is actually really small, which is why single pulls are easy, but if your pet ends up walking into the ruin itself, he <i>will</i> aggro the rest of them.</P><P>Sometimes you can go 20 minutes without a berzerker, sometimes they'll spawn several times connsecutively.</P><P>Some were light blue and one or two dark blue to me at 50. Throw in the XP for the braid quest, and it's not time completely wasted! Maybe a bubble and a half for the whole experience.</P><P>Nefariette<BR>51 Heretic<BR>E'ci</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

